'''幼态延续'''或'''幼态持续'''等（{{lang-en|neoteny}} 或 juvenilization）<ref>{{cite Dictionary.com|neoteny|access-date=April 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite American Heritage Dictionary|neoteny|access-date=April 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite Oxford Dictionaries|neoteny|us|access-date=April 21, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite Merriam-Webster|neoteny|access-date=April 21, 2019}}</ref><ref name="Montagu">Montagu, A. (1989). Growing Young. Bergin & Garvey: CT.</ref>，是延遲或減緩[[生物體|生物體]]（通常是動物）的[[生理|生理]]（或體細胞，英語：somatic）發育。 它在[[人|現代人類]]中被發現（與其他[[靈長類|靈長類]]動物相比）。<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Choi|first=Charles Q.|date=1 July 2009|title=Being More Infantile May Have Led to Bigger Brains|url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/being-more-infantile/|magazine=[[Scientific_American|Scientific American]]|access-date=2022-01-22|archive-date=2017-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808172407/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/being-more-infantile/}}</ref> 在生殖發生（英語：progenesis，或稱發育發生，英語：paedogenesis）中，[[青春期|性發育]]加速。<ref>Volkenstein, M. V. 1994. ''Physical Approaches to Biological Evolution''. Springer-Verlag: Berlin, [https://books.google.com/books?id=iiT7CAAAQBAJ&pg=PA87].</ref>

它和生殖發生都會導致 paedomorphism（或 paedomorphosis），這是一種異時性/異時發生（英語：heterochrony）。<ref name="Ridley">{{cite book|author=Ridley, Mark|url=http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/ridley/a-z/Neoteny.asp|title=Evolution|publisher=Blackwell|date=1985|access-date=2022-01-22|archive-date=2019-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526055841/http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/ridley/a-z/Neoteny.asp}}</ref> 這是成年人保留了以前只在年輕人中看到的特徵。 這種保留在[[演化生物學|演化生物學]]、[[馴化|馴化]]和[[演化發育生物學|演化發育生物學]]中很重要。

一些說法將 paedomorphism 定義為[[幼體|幼體]]特徵的保留，如[[蠑螈|蠑螈]]所呈現。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Evolution of facultative paedomorphosis|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_quarterly-review-of-biology_1994-06_69_2/page/205|first1=H.H.|journal=Quarterly Review of Biology|issue=2|doi=10.1086/418540|year=1994|volume=69|pages=205–221|last1=Whiteman}}</ref><ref name="Schell">Schell, S. C. ''Handbook of Trematodes of North America North of Mexico'', 1985, pg. 22</ref><ref>Ginetsinskaya, T.A. ''Trematodes, Their Life Cycles, Biology and Evolution''. Leningrad, USSR: Nauka 1968. Translated in 1988, [https://books.google.com/books?id=JxZDAAAAYAAJ].</ref>

== 在現代人類中 ==
與非人類靈長類動物相比，人類的幼態延續是身體發育的減慢或延遲，導致頭部大、臉平和手臂相對較短等特徵。這些幼態的變化可能是由人類演化中的[[性選擇|性選擇]]引起的。反過來，它們可能允許人類能力的發展，例如[[情感|情感]]交流。然而，人類也有相對較大的鼻子和較長的腿，兩者都是 peramorphic（而非幼態）特徵。一些演化理論家提出，幼態是[[人類演化|人類演化]]的一個關鍵特徵。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Heterochrony in human evolution: The case for neoteny reconsidered|first1=Brian T.|date=1989|journal=American Journal of Physical Anthropology|issue=S10|doi=10.1002/ajpa.1330320505|volume=32|pages=69–101|last1=Shea}}</ref> [[約翰·伯頓·桑德森·霍爾丹|約翰·伯頓·桑德森·霍爾丹]]指出，“人類的主要演化趨勢”是“兒童期的延長和[[成年人|成熟期]]的延遲。”<ref name="Montagu" /> Delbert Duane Thiessen稱“隨著早期靈長類動物演化為晚期形式，幼態延續變得更加明顯”，且靈長類動物的面部形狀的演化趨勢朝向扁平化。<ref name="Bitter">Thiessen, D.D. (1997). Bittersweet destiny: the stormy evolution of human behavior. Transaction Publishers, N.J.</ref> Doug Jones 認為，人類演化向幼態的趨勢可能是由人類演化中的性選擇引起的對年輕女性面部進行性選擇的產品”。<ref name="DJones">{{cite journal|title=Sexual selection, physical attractiveness, and facial neoteny: Cross-cultural evidence and implications [and comments and reply]|url=https://digitalcommons.usu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1601&context=fchd_facpub|first1=D.|journal=Current Anthropology|issue=5|doi=10.1086/204427|year=1995|volume=36|pages=723–748|display-authors=etal|last1=Jones|access-date=2022-01-22|archive-date=2022-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220506213054/https://digitalcommons.usu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1601&context=fchd_facpub}}</ref>

